WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.360
ARTHUR: <i>"A factory break.in, "
that's what you said.</i>

00:03.480 --> 00:05.880
We should never have got into this, Tom.

00:05.960 --> 00:07.200
On the night of June 21 st,

00:07.280 --> 00:09.720
a general strike will be called
across the city.

00:09.800 --> 00:11.120
CHARLIE: How do we know this foolish man

00:11.200 --> 00:12.920
will hand over the diamonds
when we're done?

00:13.000 --> 00:15.080
We don't. But that's another business.

00:15.160 --> 00:16.920
LINDA: When this business is done,
it will all be over.

00:17.000 --> 00:18.160
And afterwards,

00:18.240 --> 00:20.680
you and Arthur can begin your new life.

00:20.760 --> 00:22.720
So there are three cellars
underneath the house.

00:22.800 --> 00:24.120
There's a tunnel here that runs

00:24.200 --> 00:27.040
from the house, underneath the river,
to an underground strong room.

00:27.120 --> 00:30.520
We need our tunnel to run from here
and hit the strong room, direct.

00:31.120 --> 00:32.480
MICHAEL: I need to speak
to you about the Priest.

00:32.600 --> 00:34.760
(CHILDREN SCREAMING)

00:37.360 --> 00:39.800
MICHAEL: <i>I will shoot him myself Tommy.</i>

00:39.960 --> 00:43.680
I swear to God,
if my son pulls the trigger,

00:44.640 --> 00:47.800
I will bring this whole organisation
down around your ears.

00:51.280 --> 00:53.280
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:19.720 --> 01:21.480
(INAUDIBLE)

01:36.400 --> 01:40.400
Welcome to the opening
of the Grace Shelby Institute

01:40.520 --> 01:43.920
for non-insured children of the poor.

01:44.520 --> 01:48.280
I would very much like you to
join me in thanking the man

01:48.960 --> 01:52.040
that made the founding of this
establishment actually possible.

01:52.720 --> 01:54.400
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:55.520 --> 01:56.800
Mr Thomas Shelby.

01:57.120 --> 01:58.960
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

02:01.640 --> 02:02.640
ARTHUR: Speech!

02:03.440 --> 02:05.440
Come on, speech!

02:12.120 --> 02:13.960
-(CHARLES WHINING)
-Aw!

02:14.280 --> 02:16.960
ARTHUR: Say it, Tom. Say it to 'em!

02:18.520 --> 02:22.800
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

02:27.200 --> 02:30.280
Erm, I didn't come here today to
make a speech, but I will say this.

02:30.760 --> 02:32.640
These children are now safe.

02:33.360 --> 02:35.880
In our care, they will be safe.

02:36.880 --> 02:39.640
Because we are from the same
cold streets as they are.

02:40.280 --> 02:44.640
And in our care, they won't be
shipped away to the colonies,

02:45.960 --> 02:47.680
or separated from kin,

02:48.240 --> 02:51.880
or made to work for men
in their various ways.

02:52.680 --> 02:55.360
They will grow up here, at home...

02:56.520 --> 02:57.800
loved...

02:58.920 --> 03:00.320
in Birmingham.

03:02.320 --> 03:03.920
Because this is our city.

03:04.080 --> 03:07.120
By order of the Peaky Blinders.

03:07.200 --> 03:08.200
ARTHUR: Hail!

03:08.440 --> 03:09.440
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

03:25.440 --> 03:29.200
Now let us sing <i>immortal, Invisible.</i>

03:30.600 --> 03:33.640
(PIANO PLAYING)

03:35.560 --> 03:38.240
(AUDIENCE SINGING <i>IMMORTAL, INVISIBLE</i>
INDISTINCTLY <i>AT</i> DISTANCE )

03:42.600 --> 03:44.320
You hear that, Grace?

03:46.560 --> 03:47.840
(DOOR OPENING)

03:49.240 --> 03:51.600
The absence of my invitation
for this event

03:51.680 --> 03:54.200
was obviously an oversight
on your part, Mr Shelby.

03:57.240 --> 04:00.680
Look, I have the keys.
I have allocated myself an office.

04:01.280 --> 04:03.760
Just there,
two doors in from the street,

04:03.840 --> 04:08.200
it's the one that already has the stove
and the crucifixion on the window.

04:08.280 --> 04:09.720
Mr Shelby?

04:11.080 --> 04:14.080
It is the one that has the crucifixion
on the window in orange and red,

04:14.160 --> 04:15.720
that will be my office.

04:16.280 --> 04:20.840
And I will take them to
Saint Aloysius for confession.

04:20.920 --> 04:25.920
You do understand these keys are
part of our broader arrangement?

04:33.160 --> 04:37.720
In the next 24 hours, you will do
exactly as you have been instructed.

04:38.280 --> 04:40.600
You will not deviate, you'll not fail.

04:50.520 --> 04:52.320
MICHAEL: Come on, little fellas.

04:52.400 --> 04:57.040
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

04:58.120 --> 04:59.280
BOY: Ow!

04:59.400 --> 05:01.040
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

05:07.040 --> 05:08.040
The, uh...

05:09.520 --> 05:12.880
The Lord Mayor would like you to
come and eat cake and drink some tea.

05:25.680 --> 05:27.240
(SIGHS)

05:37.400 --> 05:40.120
ADA: Tommy says, "Mingle and smile."

05:41.360 --> 05:42.760
It must be the trains.

05:42.840 --> 05:44.040
ADA: No Ruben?

05:44.120 --> 05:46.760
Do you know any other guests
from London who have not turned up?

05:46.960 --> 05:49.040
Some, I think. Yes.

05:49.120 --> 05:52.360
Pol, I'm paid by the company now,
so I have to talk to other people.

05:52.440 --> 05:56.800
So you have moved from horses to
automobiles in just four years?

05:56.920 --> 05:59.200
When you ship to New York
you pay a higher dock duty.

05:59.320 --> 06:01.400
You should consider coming with us
through Boston.

06:01.600 --> 06:04.360
JOHN: I just spoke to Johnny Dogs.
He said the tunnel's hit heavy clay.

06:04.440 --> 06:05.840
-It's slowing him down.
-How long?

06:05.920 --> 06:07.480
Two days before they hit the wall.

06:07.560 --> 06:09.520
Tell him to dig a sinkhole
to drain the clay.

06:09.640 --> 06:11.800
He's asked if you could go down
and have a look yourself, Tom.

06:12.000 --> 06:13.600
I told him, wild horses
wouldn't get you down.

06:13.680 --> 06:15.040
-ARTHUR: Hmm.
-(SIGHS) Yes.

06:15.160 --> 06:18.960
Mr Shelby, I'd just like to say that
I wish I had met your dear wife

06:19.040 --> 06:20.480
before she was taken from us.

06:20.560 --> 06:24.480
And I would like to allocate
an hour a day of each of my lady's time

06:24.560 --> 06:26.240
to make winter clothes
for the little ones.

06:26.400 --> 06:29.800
Speak to my secretary, Ms Stark,
in the grey hat. She knows my diary.

06:30.000 --> 06:31.440
Fuck me, Tom.
I don't know how you do it.

06:31.520 --> 06:32.640
Incoming.

06:32.720 --> 06:33.880
-Mr Shelby?
-Yes?

06:33.960 --> 06:36.360
Aw. Your little boy
looks so much like you.

06:36.440 --> 06:38.520
He does, yes.
He's a little rascal, isn't he?

06:38.600 --> 06:42.360
Mr Shelby, would it be too inconvenient
to steal you for a moment?

06:42.440 --> 06:44.360
No, no. No inconvenience at all.

06:44.440 --> 06:46.320
-(CHARLES CRYING)
-ADA: Tommy, I am sorry. He wants you.

06:46.400 --> 06:48.680
-Aw, come here, Charlie.
-There's Daddy.

06:49.040 --> 06:50.080
Oh, little boy.

06:50.160 --> 06:54.360
So lovely to see a man
willing to hold his child in public.

06:54.440 --> 06:56.040
From the members of

06:56.120 --> 06:59.040
-the Moseley War Widow's Institute.
-Ooh, watch this!

06:59.200 --> 07:02.160
Made by Mr Winslow himself
of Winslow Castings.

07:02.240 --> 07:03.280
Look at that!

07:03.360 --> 07:06.000
From a photograph of your
horse that ran at the derby.

07:06.080 --> 07:07.240
Oh, that is very kind.

07:07.320 --> 07:08.920
-Thank you very much.
-Grace's Secret.

07:09.040 --> 07:10.680
-(CHARLES CONTINUES CRYING)
-Charlie.

07:10.760 --> 07:12.720
Would you mind holding it for us

07:12.800 --> 07:14.680
so that we can have a photograph
for the gazette?

07:14.760 --> 07:18.760
-(CHARLES CRYING LOUDLY)
-(SHUSHING) Hey, hey, hey.

07:18.840 --> 07:20.760
Oh, thank you. Thank you.
Thank you very much.

07:20.840 --> 07:22.080
Thank you very much.

07:22.160 --> 07:23.520
Thank you, Mr Shelby.

07:23.600 --> 07:26.600
-Not at all.
-Thank you.

07:26.680 --> 07:28.560
Thank you for your time, ladies.

07:28.640 --> 07:31.840
Thank you. Thank you for your time.
Thank you. Thank you.

07:36.920 --> 07:38.400
Where's Charles, Ada?

07:38.480 --> 07:39.880
I gave him to you.

07:39.960 --> 07:42.720
-Where is he?
-I don't know.

07:42.800 --> 07:44.080
Boys.

07:44.880 --> 07:46.120
-Have you seen Charlie?
-ARTHUR: Eh?

07:46.240 --> 07:47.240
JOHN: I haven't seen him.
ARTHUR: I don't know.

07:47.320 --> 07:48.320
He is playing, ain't he?

07:48.480 --> 07:50.960
Pol, where's Charles?

07:51.040 --> 07:52.880
Lizzie, where is Charlie?

07:52.960 --> 07:54.760
-I don't know.
-Where is he?

07:54.840 --> 07:56.280
Back Door. Kitchen.

07:56.360 --> 07:57.960
Get to Blake Street, where the cars are.

07:58.040 --> 08:00.800
Tommy! Someone said they saw a nurse
take him through the back door.

08:00.880 --> 08:01.880
-Fuck.
-What nurse?

08:01.960 --> 08:02.960
I don't know. Go.

08:10.160 --> 08:12.240
(GRUNTING)

08:16.040 --> 08:17.240
-Arthur.
-What?

08:17.360 --> 08:19.360
Somebody said they saw a woman
and a kid getting into a car.

08:19.440 --> 08:20.560
Ah, fuck!

08:25.920 --> 08:27.320
Charlie!

08:29.400 --> 08:31.480
Charlie!

08:31.560 --> 08:32.800
Charlie!

08:32.880 --> 08:34.960
TOMMY: John.

08:35.040 --> 08:36.640
-Where is he?
-ARTHUR: John.

08:36.720 --> 08:38.280
TOMMY: Arthur.
ARTHUR: Go find Moss.

08:38.360 --> 08:42.000
-Arthur, where is he? Where is he?
-Junctions, block them all off.

08:42.080 --> 08:43.600
-Tell me.
-Someone took him.

08:43.680 --> 08:44.800
All right.

08:44.880 --> 08:46.960
Hey, listen to me!
They put him in a car.

08:47.120 --> 08:49.120
They put him in a car and drove south.

08:50.600 --> 08:52.240
We've got roadblocks and spotters.

08:52.360 --> 08:55.000
I'll set up shop
and put every man we have

08:55.080 --> 08:57.640
-on the junctions from here to Maypole.
-Yeah. Yeah. Right. You do that.

08:57.720 --> 08:59.200
-But you have got to go to the office.
-Yeah.

08:59.280 --> 09:01.080
You've got to sit by the phone.

09:01.160 --> 09:02.720
-Whoever took him is going to call.
-Right. Of course.

09:02.800 --> 09:03.840
Polly!

09:04.520 --> 09:05.960
Let's go, Pol.

09:06.320 --> 09:09.080
Stay by that phone.
Me and John will cover the roads.

09:09.480 --> 09:11.200
TOMMY: I need Michael
at the Maypole junction.

09:13.320 --> 09:15.400
I need Moss to block
all the roads south.

09:20.800 --> 09:23.560
Give me Moss. Gone where?

09:30.360 --> 09:32.440
-Tommy...
-It's them.

09:32.640 --> 09:34.120
-Who?
-It's fucking them.

09:34.200 --> 09:35.720
Look, it might just be
some random woman.

09:35.800 --> 09:38.200
-Because sometimes women go mad...
-No, it is them.

09:38.880 --> 09:39.880
Did you break the phone?

09:46.000 --> 09:48.080
He broke the phone.

09:48.160 --> 09:49.400
It's all right,
we have got another phone.

09:49.480 --> 09:51.080
-ADA: Tommy?
-Ada?

09:52.680 --> 09:54.680
There's someone outside, a priest.

09:54.760 --> 09:56.520
Stay here, Pol, stay here.
Don't do anything.

10:11.080 --> 10:14.840
We have your son.
Get in the car.

10:22.000 --> 10:23.200
TOMMY:
First.

10:23.680 --> 10:25.000
Is he safe?

10:25.080 --> 10:27.120
Of course he's safe.

10:27.240 --> 10:29.200
All children are dear to me.

10:30.440 --> 10:32.680
You have all the cards.

10:32.760 --> 10:35.760
Tell me what you want me to do
and I will certainly do it.

10:35.840 --> 10:38.240
You ever drive one of these beasts?

10:38.320 --> 10:40.240
I am asking you to conduct business.

10:40.320 --> 10:42.200
Of course, I borrowed it.

10:42.320 --> 10:46.280
Lent it by a Lord
for the duration of this business.

10:46.360 --> 10:51.760
I will certainly do what you
need me to do with no complaint.

10:51.840 --> 10:55.600
We were forced into
doing this awful thing.

10:55.680 --> 11:01.120
We did warn you that your son would be
in danger if you deviated from the plan.

11:01.200 --> 11:02.400
It was you who made a mistake.

11:02.480 --> 11:03.640
-You understand?
-Yes.

11:03.760 --> 11:05.920
What mistake did you make?
Do you even know?

11:06.160 --> 11:08.480
Tell me what you want me to do.

11:08.800 --> 11:12.080
-You made a deal with our enemies.
-I will do what needs to be done.

11:12.160 --> 11:16.840
You went behind our backs to stop
the Soviets from blowing up the train.

11:19.480 --> 11:22.000
But it's all right. It's all right.

11:22.080 --> 11:24.080
We've rectified your mistake.

11:25.200 --> 11:27.320
You ask me, "What do I need to do?"

11:27.880 --> 11:31.360
Well, here is what you need to do,
you fucking mongrel, you...

11:36.240 --> 11:38.800
Since the Bolsheviks will not
be blowing up the train,

11:39.280 --> 11:40.720
you will blow up the train yourself.

11:42.800 --> 11:44.960
It has always been about the explosion

11:45.400 --> 11:49.160
from the beginning.
The bang. The outrage.

11:49.240 --> 11:50.680
Understand?

11:52.720 --> 11:56.160
Those are notes and fragments
for you to scatter in the wreckage,

11:56.240 --> 11:58.480
implicating named officials
from the Soviet Embassy.

11:59.400 --> 12:01.120
I will scatter them. It will be done.

12:01.200 --> 12:02.440
Good.

12:02.840 --> 12:06.000
Our friends at <i>The Times</i> and
the <i>Daily Mailwill</i> do the rest.

12:06.080 --> 12:08.120
And once the British government

12:08.200 --> 12:11.560
cuts diplomatic relations
with the Soviet Union,

12:11.680 --> 12:14.040
that will be our mission accomplished.

12:14.120 --> 12:16.720
You would have been
part of a fine adventure.

12:18.680 --> 12:21.720
To help with the outrage,
we need people to die in the explosion.

12:22.800 --> 12:23.880
How many?

12:25.680 --> 12:28.880
Let's say... six.

12:29.960 --> 12:32.320
Rail workers, perhaps,
men from the factory.

12:33.880 --> 12:36.040
(MOUTHING)

12:39.040 --> 12:44.600
And I want my son returned to me
within an hour of the explosion.

12:45.840 --> 12:47.480
Oh, it's conditions now, is it?

12:48.000 --> 12:50.080
We need to fix the
handover in advance.

12:50.160 --> 12:53.640
I haven't finished
with you yet, Mr Shelby.

12:54.760 --> 12:58.400
We also hear
that you are digging a tunnel.

12:58.640 --> 13:01.560
Mining for precious stones
under Wilderness House.

13:05.040 --> 13:08.480
I'm told they have a Fabergé
in the strong room.

13:08.560 --> 13:12.960
The Lilies of the Valley Egg
made in 1898.

13:13.040 --> 13:16.600
One of the Odd Fellows has a wife
who's obsessed with Fabergé.

13:16.680 --> 13:18.200
He wants to give her the egg
for her birthday.

13:18.280 --> 13:19.440
Then he will have it.

13:21.600 --> 13:25.160
And the Economic League will take
all of the jewels that you steal,

13:25.280 --> 13:28.360
to cover our considerable expenses.

13:28.520 --> 13:30.920
The fight against Communism
is not cheap you know.

13:31.760 --> 13:34.600
-So if you want to see your...
-I will give you all the jewels.

13:35.920 --> 13:38.040
A bang first.

13:38.120 --> 13:43.160
Then bring everything that you
have stolen to your office at dawn.

13:43.240 --> 13:45.200
No. No, I'm, uh...

13:45.840 --> 13:48.080
I'll not be able to get the
jewels to you by dawn.

13:48.160 --> 13:49.280
The tunnel has hit clay.

13:49.400 --> 13:53.400
If the St. Andrew's clock strikes
5:00 a.m. on the night of the robbery

13:53.520 --> 13:55.960
and we don't have everything
that we asked for,

13:56.080 --> 13:57.720
the bell will be tolling for your boy.

13:57.880 --> 13:59.400
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

14:01.280 --> 14:04.080
Now get out of my fucking car.

14:06.960 --> 14:09.480
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

14:16.960 --> 14:18.720
-TOMMY: Where's Linda?
-With Esme.

14:18.800 --> 14:20.160
Esme's water broke.

14:20.240 --> 14:23.400
I was just with her. Running around,
fucking broke her water.

14:23.480 --> 14:25.280
-Where is Finn?
-Out with the young ones,

14:25.720 --> 14:27.400
looking for the Riley.
We couldn't reach him.

14:27.480 --> 14:29.000
I need to know who spoke.

14:29.080 --> 14:30.880
Our enemies know everything. Everything.

14:31.680 --> 14:34.760
I need to know who spoke about business
outside of the family.

14:34.840 --> 14:37.480
I need to know who spoke
and who they spoke to, now.

14:37.560 --> 14:39.600
-Tommy, listen, uh...
-Your wife, Arthur?

14:42.160 --> 14:46.720
I am going to tell myself that
you are not thinking straight.

14:46.800 --> 14:48.480
Your mind is not clear.

14:49.080 --> 14:52.040
Or Esme getting cash
for cocaine, eh, John?

14:52.120 --> 14:53.160
Fuck!

14:53.920 --> 14:55.480
All of a sudden,
back in the family, Ada.

14:55.560 --> 14:58.040
Eh? That is a surprise.
Out of the blue.

14:58.400 --> 14:59.480
On whose orders?

14:59.560 --> 15:01.720
POLLY: Tommy, this is
not helping find him.

15:01.800 --> 15:02.800
And you and your painter.

15:04.120 --> 15:05.480
You said he knows you.

15:05.920 --> 15:08.400
Things developed. You talked.

15:08.480 --> 15:12.560
If anyone has talked about
the tunnel to anyone else,

15:12.640 --> 15:14.800
I need to know,
and I need to know this second.

15:14.880 --> 15:17.160
-What about your clay kickers?
-ARTHUR: Hmm.

15:17.240 --> 15:18.520
Drunk in a pub.

15:18.800 --> 15:20.400
I'd trust those men with my life.

15:20.480 --> 15:23.040
-More than you trust us?
-Yes.

15:23.120 --> 15:24.680
As of an hour ago, yes.

15:25.520 --> 15:27.400
JOHN: Why is Michael not in
this fucking line-up, anyway?

15:27.480 --> 15:29.040
POLLY: You leave Michael out of this.
JOHN: Oh, yes?

15:29.120 --> 15:30.760
-ARTHUR: No, he should be here.
-I fucking don't even know him.

15:30.840 --> 15:32.880
And I have only fucking known him
for fucking three years.

15:32.960 --> 15:34.040
POLLY: No, he is not going
to be your whipping boy.

15:34.120 --> 15:35.240
JOHN: I don't even fucking know the boy.

15:36.560 --> 15:39.000
I never told Michael
about the Lilies of the Valley.

15:40.920 --> 15:44.720
The only people I told about
the Fabergé eggs are in this room.

15:50.040 --> 15:52.280
Tommy, I want you to know
that I came back for love...

15:55.680 --> 15:58.000
and common sense.

16:02.640 --> 16:04.720
And Esme's got no need for extra cash.

16:10.560 --> 16:12.280
And you bring my wife into this,

16:13.480 --> 16:16.000
means we speak
when this business is done.

16:18.280 --> 16:20.000
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

16:20.840 --> 16:22.040
John, Arthur,

16:23.160 --> 16:27.600
I need 50 sticks of BSA dynamite
and 300 yards of cable

16:27.680 --> 16:31.640
and six detonators by midday tomorrow.

16:31.720 --> 16:33.480
And this is evidence.
I need you to scatter it.

16:34.760 --> 16:36.840
We're blowing up a train,
and people are going to die.

16:52.720 --> 16:54.160
(DOOR CLOSING)

16:54.680 --> 16:56.480
Ruben and I talked about many things.

16:58.600 --> 17:00.000
(DOOR OPENING)

17:00.120 --> 17:01.360
But not that. Not ever.

17:01.480 --> 17:03.320
-(DOOR CLOSING)
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

17:03.920 --> 17:05.240
Tommy, I'm sorry I'm late.

17:05.320 --> 17:07.400
We looked everywhere,
all the way up to Hay Mills.

17:07.480 --> 17:08.480
We saw nothing.

17:09.320 --> 17:12.840
Put four cans of petrol in the boot
of my car and bring it round.

17:13.280 --> 17:15.040
Put cigarettes and a lamp in the box.

17:15.400 --> 17:16.520
And fetch Michael. I need him.

17:18.880 --> 17:20.600
-(DOOR OPENING)
-Ada told me he gave you red wine.

17:20.720 --> 17:21.760
(DOOR CLOSING)

17:21.840 --> 17:24.160
I imagine you can't remember
half of what you talked about.

17:24.240 --> 17:25.760
He was never interested in business.

17:27.520 --> 17:29.760
He came to you at my wedding.

17:31.840 --> 17:34.200
He pursued you. Sought you out.

17:35.840 --> 17:39.160
Why would an educated man of his
standing do something like that?

17:42.400 --> 17:45.040
-You mean, to a woman like me?
-Yes.

17:49.960 --> 17:53.520
I've done the odds on all of you.
Even's it's him.

17:54.720 --> 17:56.760
There is another possibility,
but even's it's him.

18:03.520 --> 18:05.840
(DOOR OPENING, CLOSING)

18:07.920 --> 18:10.440
(POLLY SNIFFLING)

18:21.480 --> 18:23.280
(SOBBING)

18:31.400 --> 18:32.760
(GRUNTS)

18:33.840 --> 18:35.600
(SCREAMS)

19:03.600 --> 19:04.960
(ALFIE GROANS)

19:05.040 --> 19:06.400
ALFIE: Bloody hell.

19:07.520 --> 19:09.480
(ALFIE GROANS)

19:14.080 --> 19:15.680
I asked that you come alone and unarmed.

19:15.760 --> 19:18.280
Yeah, well, alone I ain't
never gonna do, am I?

19:18.400 --> 19:20.280
And as for the cane,
don't worry about it.

19:20.400 --> 19:21.840
That is just my sciatica.

19:21.920 --> 19:25.160
It always plays up around the
winter and the summer solstice.

19:25.440 --> 19:27.280
What have you got for me, Alfie?

19:27.360 --> 19:28.560
ALFIE: What did you
bring me out here for?

19:29.160 --> 19:31.440
This is on the way
to somewhere I need to be in a hurry.

19:31.560 --> 19:34.200
-Mmm.
-What have you got for me?

19:34.280 --> 19:37.560
Well, seeing as you were prepared
to pay such an exorbitant amount

19:37.640 --> 19:41.640
for this information, I decided
to give you value for money.

19:42.000 --> 19:45.920
So here are the names
of all the men in England

19:46.080 --> 19:49.880
whom I would approach, right,
if I had a Fabergé egg for sale.

19:50.000 --> 19:51.560
Here you go.

19:51.680 --> 19:54.560
And then, here's all
the men on that list,

19:54.680 --> 19:56.640
you know, who would buy
the old Fabergé egg,

19:56.800 --> 19:59.000
even if they knew that
that item was stolen.

19:59.120 --> 20:00.120
Here.

20:00.720 --> 20:03.840
Then comes your curious
fucking gyppo question.

20:03.920 --> 20:05.400
I won't ask but, erm...

20:06.280 --> 20:10.920
Here is a list of the men
who would buy a Fabergé

20:11.000 --> 20:13.320
because of their wife's obsession.

20:22.480 --> 20:26.200
Ah, yes. Thank you, Mr Shelby.
It's lovely doing business with you.

20:44.400 --> 20:45.880
You left a name off the list, Alfie.

20:45.960 --> 20:47.280
-Did I?
-Yeah.

20:47.600 --> 20:49.920
I've already spoken to my people
in the jewellery quarter.

20:50.000 --> 20:52.120
Experienced dealers.

20:52.200 --> 20:55.080
They tell me there are only
three men in Britain

20:55.160 --> 20:57.040
whose wives are obsessed with Fabergé.

20:57.120 --> 20:58.840
Makes them good customers.

20:58.920 --> 21:00.800
You missed the richest one off the list.

21:00.880 --> 21:02.800
Yeah, well, if you knew already

21:02.880 --> 21:06.000
how come you dragged me all the way
out into the fucking oggin, mate?

21:06.080 --> 21:07.920
Two reasons. Reason one.

21:08.880 --> 21:12.200
By withholding a name
that you most certainly know,

21:12.280 --> 21:15.880
you've proven to me that you have
done a deal with the Odd Fellows.

21:15.960 --> 21:18.720
It was you who told them
about the tunnel.

21:18.800 --> 21:23.040
You who told them about the
fucking deal with the Soviets.

21:23.120 --> 21:24.120
Reason two.

21:24.800 --> 21:27.400
The name of the man that you're
withholding must be my enemy

21:27.560 --> 21:29.480
otherwise,
you wouldn't be protecting him.

21:30.080 --> 21:31.400
He is now a man I can use.

21:32.160 --> 21:35.040
Listen, sweetie, you can't take a man...

21:35.120 --> 21:37.880
You gave information
in exchange for a share.

21:37.960 --> 21:40.120
Tommy... Tommy there were
things in that treasury, right,

21:40.200 --> 21:41.880
that God himself, He spoke to me,

21:41.960 --> 21:44.240
and He said, "Alfie, you are
meant to have these things."

21:44.320 --> 21:45.480
You crossed the line, Alfie.

21:46.280 --> 21:48.160
-You fucking what?
-You crossed the line.

21:48.240 --> 21:51.120
-"The line"?
-They are using my boy!

21:56.360 --> 21:57.640
Did you fucking know?

21:57.720 --> 21:59.560
Yeah, I knew, you know.

21:59.640 --> 22:03.440
But damned as I am, it made
no fucking difference to me, mate.

22:04.720 --> 22:06.120
(GROANS)

22:08.160 --> 22:09.400
(CHOKING)

22:10.240 --> 22:12.280
(GASPING)
Fucking hell, Tommy!

22:14.640 --> 22:17.480
ALFIE: Oh! Crying out loud.

22:18.040 --> 22:19.640
What the fuck is going on?

22:24.040 --> 22:25.720
What is the matter with you, Tommy, eh?

22:26.200 --> 22:28.320
Eh? You've gone fucking angry,
ain't you?

22:28.480 --> 22:30.520
-Yeah, I got fucking angry...
-It's in your fucking head, man.

22:30.600 --> 22:32.960
-Come on, man!
-MICHAEL: This bastard deserves it!

22:33.040 --> 22:34.240
ALFIE: He's nuts!

22:34.320 --> 22:36.160
It's in your fucking head, son.

22:36.240 --> 22:38.040
I know this bastard deserves it.

22:38.800 --> 22:40.160
I fucking know.

22:40.280 --> 22:43.760
But if you kill him now,
the truce with the London outfits

22:43.840 --> 22:45.240
will be blown to
fucking pieces, all right?

22:45.320 --> 22:47.800
-Michael. Michael.
-Don't worry about that truce, kid,

22:47.880 --> 22:49.960
right, because it fell apart.

22:52.240 --> 22:54.880
You got nothing to worry about when it
comes to the ol' scary London boys.

22:54.960 --> 22:56.640
Which fucking side are you on, Alfie?

22:56.760 --> 22:59.080
I do not give a fuck right now, kid.
All right?

23:02.360 --> 23:06.680
I do not want him to spare me
because of some fucking peace pact.

23:08.240 --> 23:14.920
I want him to acknowledge that
his anger is un-fucking justified!

23:15.000 --> 23:18.680
I want him to acknowledge
that he who fights by the sword,

23:18.760 --> 23:20.760
he fucking dies by it, Tommy.

23:21.760 --> 23:24.280
So what, they took
your boy did they, eh?

23:24.360 --> 23:25.560
They have got your boy?

23:25.680 --> 23:28.960
What fucking "line" am I
supposed to have crossed?

23:32.080 --> 23:35.160
How many fathers, right,
how many sons, yeah,

23:35.240 --> 23:39.960
have you cut, killed, murdered
fucking butchered, innocent and guilty?

23:40.040 --> 23:42.000
You are going straight to
fucking hell, ain't ya?

23:42.080 --> 23:44.680
Just like me!

23:44.760 --> 23:48.920
You fucking stand there,
you, judging me,

23:49.000 --> 23:53.040
stand there and talk to me about
crossing some fucking line.

23:55.920 --> 23:58.200
If you pull that trigger, right,

23:58.280 --> 24:01.360
you pull that trigger
for a fucking hon our able reason.

24:01.440 --> 24:05.200
Like an hon our able man,
not like some fucking civilian

24:05.440 --> 24:10.120
that does not understand
the wicked way of our world, mate.

24:12.000 --> 24:13.160
MICHAEL: Look, Tommy,

24:14.480 --> 24:17.560
the killing of Alfie Solomons
is not going to help.

24:19.200 --> 24:21.880
This will be very bad for business.

24:25.000 --> 24:26.400
Michael,

24:29.360 --> 24:32.520
go and call Inspector Moss.
Tell him it's Palmer.

24:39.640 --> 24:41.560
Well said, Alfie.

24:42.360 --> 24:43.680
Well said.

24:45.120 --> 24:46.280
(STAMMERING)

24:46.360 --> 24:47.800
(SIGHS)

24:50.360 --> 24:52.200
I did not know about your boy, though.

24:52.720 --> 24:54.040
I know.

24:54.920 --> 24:56.360
I saw.

25:12.760 --> 25:14.320
(DOOR CREAKING)

25:16.480 --> 25:17.680
RUBEN: Hello?

25:21.760 --> 25:22.960
(DOOR CLOSING)

25:42.640 --> 25:44.160
(GUN COCKING)

25:47.480 --> 25:48.640
Good Lord.

25:54.960 --> 25:57.880
(BREATH TREMBLING) Polly...

26:00.000 --> 26:01.680
Why didn't you come?

26:03.360 --> 26:05.680
I was going to get on the train
last night but then I...

26:07.280 --> 26:10.040
I realised I simply I wasn't
ready to enter your world.

26:11.880 --> 26:13.200
Good God. I'm shaking.

26:13.360 --> 26:14.360
Good.

26:17.360 --> 26:21.000
But now, I am ready.
I have been searching all night for you.

26:22.560 --> 26:25.400
Polly, whatever you have been told,
it is not true.

26:30.240 --> 26:31.560
-(UNCOCKS GUN)
-(EXHALES)

26:42.480 --> 26:43.880
The painting was wrong.

26:49.320 --> 26:51.520
She was too sure of herself...

26:55.240 --> 26:57.080
and I'm not.

27:00.520 --> 27:02.240
Not any more.

27:04.920 --> 27:06.560
I can paint another.

27:08.520 --> 27:10.480
(SOBBING)

27:10.960 --> 27:12.520
RUBEN: Oh, Polly.

27:13.080 --> 27:14.400
(SIGHS)

27:15.480 --> 27:16.840
Oh, Polly.

27:16.920 --> 27:18.840
POLLY: What the fuck am I doing?

27:24.160 --> 27:26.040
I want a dull life.

27:26.120 --> 27:29.600
I want you. I want you. I want you.

27:29.680 --> 27:34.480
I want you to paint me in a dress
that I bought in a shop.

27:36.640 --> 27:38.120
We have a life?

27:41.720 --> 27:43.120
I think so.

27:43.960 --> 27:45.400
(LAUGHING)

27:47.240 --> 27:49.080
(PHONE RINGING)

27:51.440 --> 27:52.800
Hello?

28:02.680 --> 28:04.000
PALMER: I demand to see my solicitor.

28:04.080 --> 28:06.320
I have a right to have him here.

28:06.480 --> 28:07.880
ARTHUR: Gilbert Palmer.

28:07.960 --> 28:09.880
I want to talk to you
about a missing kid.

28:10.200 --> 28:11.720
(PALMER STRUGGLING)

28:11.800 --> 28:14.880
We are Peaky Blinders.

28:15.080 --> 28:16.560
-Where is he?
-(GASPING)

28:17.000 --> 28:18.320
-Deep breath.
-(MUFFLED TALKING)

28:18.480 --> 28:19.560
-(MUFFLED SCREAMS)
-(ROPE STRAINING)

28:19.640 --> 28:20.760
Where is he?

28:25.880 --> 28:27.360
(CAR APPROACHING)

28:40.760 --> 28:42.880
TOMMY: Johnny! Johnny!

28:42.960 --> 28:44.520
What the fuck are you doing here, Tommy?

28:44.640 --> 28:46.000
They've taken my boy, Johnny.

28:46.160 --> 28:47.600
Everything's fucking changed.

28:47.720 --> 28:49.800
I have the hole dug before midnight
or he's gone.

28:49.960 --> 28:51.040
Do you hear me?

28:51.600 --> 28:53.720
JOHNNY: Are you not going
after Charles yourself?

28:53.960 --> 28:55.280
Tommy?

29:16.440 --> 29:18.000
(SNIFFLES)

29:30.000 --> 29:31.240
MICHAEL: Well, I was at...

29:32.880 --> 29:35.360
This morning, I was out
on the road with Tommy.

29:37.760 --> 29:38.840
I killed a man.

29:40.360 --> 29:42.080
Well, he needed cover.
I was all he had.

29:43.120 --> 29:44.600
So what did he give you?

29:47.080 --> 29:49.240
He said it was good for close range.

29:50.200 --> 29:51.560
You're better with my Smith & Wesson.

29:51.640 --> 29:56.000
No, no. This is mine now.
It feels part of my hand.

29:57.800 --> 29:58.920
Where'd you hit him?

30:00.840 --> 30:02.320
I hit him in the side of the head.

30:02.400 --> 30:03.720
How was you when he went down?

30:03.800 --> 30:05.440
Tommy said I did all right.

30:06.560 --> 30:08.800
This is where we think Charles
is being held.

30:11.600 --> 30:15.560
They're not expecting anybody,
so he should be alone.

30:23.280 --> 30:24.280
There is two good men there.

30:26.520 --> 30:28.160
You do what they say.

30:29.920 --> 30:31.880
But I fire the bullet. All right?

30:33.160 --> 30:34.600
Yes, you can be there.

30:35.480 --> 30:37.040
But it's better if they do it.

30:38.280 --> 30:40.520
See, these are experienced men, Michael.

30:44.240 --> 30:48.320
When you're sure the kid is safe,
you call Finn.

30:49.440 --> 30:50.680
All right.

30:57.680 --> 30:58.920
Come on, boys.

31:05.880 --> 31:07.120
(DOOR CLOSES)

31:27.360 --> 31:28.640
HUGHES: Hello there.

31:31.360 --> 31:33.360
There you go. How's that?

31:34.480 --> 31:36.400
Like a spoon? A shiny spoon?

31:37.320 --> 31:38.880
Do you want to hold the spoon there?

31:40.600 --> 31:42.360
(GRUNTING)

31:50.960 --> 31:55.480
All out, boys! Wild cat strike!

31:55.560 --> 31:57.560
(ALL YELLING)

32:04.440 --> 32:06.600
ARTHUR: This locomotive

32:09.320 --> 32:12.280
couples in 15 minutes.

32:14.120 --> 32:16.440
If we don't hear word by 10:00,

32:19.280 --> 32:20.440
we blow it up.

32:22.960 --> 32:24.560
There are men on board, Arthur.

32:26.080 --> 32:28.920
Yeah. Six men on board, Charlie.

32:30.040 --> 32:32.760
Driver, stoker

32:34.640 --> 32:36.400
and four men
I hand-picked myself.

32:41.000 --> 32:42.960
Me and John picked those men.

32:45.840 --> 32:47.960
So it is me and John
who will pull the switch.

32:54.480 --> 32:56.280
The rest of you men can go home.

32:57.520 --> 32:59.000
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS)

33:01.600 --> 33:03.200
LETSO: Tommy. Tommy.

33:03.520 --> 33:05.440
He has got the shakes,
help me with him.

33:07.120 --> 33:09.080
TOMMY: Get him out. Get him out.

33:09.240 --> 33:10.680
LETSO: We are bringing him through.

33:10.760 --> 33:12.560
TOMMY: We need to move. Now.

33:36.800 --> 33:38.840
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

33:51.480 --> 33:52.600
MICHAEL: You wait here.

33:55.040 --> 33:56.200
I'll do the killing.

34:00.080 --> 34:01.480
That is a fucking order.

34:27.960 --> 34:29.040
You move too fast, Thomas.

34:31.400 --> 34:33.640
(STRUCTURE CREAKING)

34:39.040 --> 34:40.080
We need more timber.

34:40.160 --> 34:41.960
Make it safe. I will go on.

34:42.080 --> 34:43.920
Thomas, it is too fucking wet.
It's sludge.

34:44.000 --> 34:46.000
TOMMY: Make it fucking safe,
and I'll go on!

34:46.320 --> 34:47.640
(SIGHS)

34:48.520 --> 34:49.520
Okay.

34:58.480 --> 35:00.120
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

35:19.960 --> 35:21.800
(EXHALES)

35:34.720 --> 35:35.720
(EXHALING)

35:41.560 --> 35:42.560
(CHARLES FUSSING)

35:50.240 --> 35:52.480
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

35:54.560 --> 35:56.280
What do you think you are doing, boy?

36:01.400 --> 36:02.680
Please don't.

36:03.760 --> 36:06.040
Please don't shoot.
Please don't shoot.

36:07.400 --> 36:09.320
Please don't. Please.

36:22.560 --> 36:24.040
-(MICHAEL GROANING)
-You fucking rat!

36:25.440 --> 36:26.800
What do you think you're doing?

36:27.320 --> 36:29.680
You know who you're
fuckin' messing with?

36:30.640 --> 36:31.640
(CHOKING)

36:33.520 --> 36:34.720
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

36:47.240 --> 36:48.400
LETSO: We don't have much time.

36:48.880 --> 36:51.720
I'll take your fuckin'
life from you. (GRUNTS)

36:57.280 --> 36:58.440
Let's go!

36:59.280 --> 37:00.360
(TOMMY GROANS)

37:09.000 --> 37:10.680
You are a gypsy bastard.

37:10.760 --> 37:12.040
-(GROANING)
-(MICHAEL SCREAMS)

37:15.440 --> 37:16.560
(SCREAMING)

37:30.960 --> 37:32.160
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS)

37:32.240 --> 37:33.880
Who wants to be in heaven, eh?

37:35.920 --> 37:39.160
Who want to be in heaven when you
can be sending men to fucking hell.

37:39.240 --> 37:40.880
-(CHUCKLES)
-Hey.

37:42.400 --> 37:44.680
I will do it, Arthur. Eh?

37:44.800 --> 37:45.920
I'll do it.

37:48.560 --> 37:50.680
I will take him.

37:50.760 --> 37:52.200
No, this bastard is mine.

37:52.400 --> 37:53.600
Go call Finn.

37:57.000 --> 37:58.680
I told Tommy I'd do it...

38:00.400 --> 38:01.800
so I'll do it.

38:02.640 --> 38:03.880
(SKIN SQUISHING)

38:12.120 --> 38:13.120
(PHONE RINGING)

38:15.560 --> 38:17.000
Arthur, wait!

38:17.200 --> 38:18.280
Charlie is safe.

38:18.360 --> 38:19.920
(EXPLOSION)

38:23.160 --> 38:24.280
(FINN GRUNTING)

38:48.960 --> 38:51.080
(GRUNTING)

39:02.080 --> 39:04.280
(PANTING)

39:06.560 --> 39:07.560
(EXHALES)

39:16.120 --> 39:18.040
-It's all right.
-(CHARLES COOING)

39:36.080 --> 39:37.320
(CHARLES CRYING)

39:42.840 --> 39:44.400
-Oh, God!
-Oh!

40:16.360 --> 40:17.520
Let me speak to him.

40:18.480 --> 40:21.040
-Hello, Charlie?
-(CHARLES MUMBLING)

40:21.120 --> 40:22.240
Hello, Charlie.

40:23.600 --> 40:24.720
Can you hear me?

40:25.320 --> 40:26.440
-Yeah.
-CHARLES: <i>Yeah.</i>

40:28.600 --> 40:31.080
-Yeah, you go to bed.
-(MUMBLING)

40:31.160 --> 40:32.280
Good boy.

40:43.000 --> 40:45.200
(SOBBING)

41:11.160 --> 41:12.680
Where the hell have you been?

41:14.640 --> 41:15.960
I've been out in Maypole.

41:17.640 --> 41:19.120
There has been some trouble.

41:22.640 --> 41:24.320
I can't stay.

41:29.320 --> 41:32.800
You can't stay? (BREATHING SHAKILY)

41:32.880 --> 41:34.280
Tommy needs my help.

41:36.440 --> 41:37.800
It's family business.

41:37.880 --> 41:40.720
-No, no. Please.
-I am sorry.

41:40.800 --> 41:42.000
Please.

42:14.360 --> 42:16.320
-Where is he?
-ADA: He is upstairs.

42:37.760 --> 42:39.480
(INAUDIBLE)

43:18.440 --> 43:21.960
Mr Shelby,
this is <i>MonsieurSilk.</i>

43:22.720 --> 43:25.200
He is here on behalf
of the Parisian buyers.

43:25.280 --> 43:27.240
He needs to verify the value.

43:31.240 --> 43:33.720
It was a pleasure doing business
with you these past few months.

43:44.840 --> 43:47.200
You would never steal
from your family, would you?

43:50.400 --> 43:52.240
The collection was mostly
my mother's, anyway.

43:53.120 --> 43:56.040
It is more mine than theirs,
and they would never have sold it.

43:56.320 --> 43:58.200
They would have wasted it
on a lost cause.

43:58.600 --> 44:00.360
You needed a tunnel.

44:02.320 --> 44:04.360
I need your signature
to make this sale legal.

44:05.080 --> 44:06.600
SILK: Confirmed.

44:07.400 --> 44:09.880
The original Duke Alexander
Petrovich's collection.

44:13.160 --> 44:16.200
To raise a legal bill of sale
and get this across the border,

44:17.360 --> 44:19.520
I will need an authorisation

44:19.600 --> 44:23.840
signed by yourself in the family name
in my presence.

44:24.160 --> 44:25.480
As we agreed.

44:25.880 --> 44:27.760
Half for the tunnel,
half for the signature.

44:29.480 --> 44:30.480
Where will you go?

44:31.000 --> 44:32.120
Vienna.

44:33.800 --> 44:35.320
There is a man waiting for me.

44:36.600 --> 44:37.880
Poor man.

44:38.440 --> 44:39.480
You?

44:39.880 --> 44:40.960
Birmingham.

44:42.240 --> 44:43.680
I'm going to buy a racehorse

44:46.480 --> 44:48.080
and have it trained.

45:17.160 --> 45:20.440
Also, £5,000 for the sex.

45:26.320 --> 45:27.480
(EXHALES)

45:39.560 --> 45:42.240
And five for helping you
through the grief of losing your wife.

45:53.440 --> 45:54.840
You didn't even come close.

45:57.360 --> 45:59.720
SILK: (CLEARS THROAT)
The papers are in order.

46:01.160 --> 46:03.640
Now I just need your signature
for the provenance.

46:03.720 --> 46:05.760
TATIANA: Of course. I have a pen.

46:08.120 --> 46:09.160
(GUNSHOT)

46:17.560 --> 46:19.560
At home, these jewels saw way worse.

46:21.080 --> 46:22.440
That is why they are all cursed...

46:24.360 --> 46:27.400
as are we, Mr Shelby.

46:30.920 --> 46:32.640
If you are ever in Vienna, look me up.

46:44.880 --> 46:48.080
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

47:00.120 --> 47:01.720
(DOOR OPENS)

47:03.080 --> 47:04.360
ARTHUR: Yes, yes.

47:21.360 --> 47:22.800
(DOOR CLOSES)

47:45.360 --> 47:46.560
Before I begin,

47:49.280 --> 47:51.080
I want to let you know
I made a mistake.

47:55.960 --> 47:57.240
I made a mistake,

47:58.480 --> 48:00.320
and I want to apologise
to all of you.

48:02.640 --> 48:03.920
Arthur,

48:04.640 --> 48:07.320
you warned me against getting
involved in Russian business,

48:09.080 --> 48:10.200
and you were right.

48:10.960 --> 48:12.040
Mmm.

48:13.000 --> 48:16.400
TOMMY: I doubted your wife,
for that, I am sorry.

48:17.520 --> 48:21.600
Linda, I have added 3,000 here,
in the hope you will forgive me.

48:31.560 --> 48:33.520
Apology accepted.

48:37.640 --> 48:39.800
Esme, I doubted you as well.

48:40.320 --> 48:43.440
Now John has got innocent lives
on his conscience.

48:43.520 --> 48:45.120
-Ordinary working men...
-Yeah, all right.

48:45.200 --> 48:47.640
-Esme, we got it.
-No. She is right.

48:48.960 --> 48:50.800
You and Arthur are going to
have to share that burden.

48:54.600 --> 48:56.480
But I hope the house
that you can buy with this

48:57.080 --> 48:58.480
can become a place of...

48:59.720 --> 49:00.920
contemplation

49:02.520 --> 49:04.080
and perhaps, redemption.

49:09.360 --> 49:12.120
Charlie, for lost tools
and dangerous goods

49:12.840 --> 49:14.120
and Curly's wise words.

49:15.040 --> 49:18.040
Johnny, for board and lodgings.

49:19.760 --> 49:20.880
Lizzie.

49:27.560 --> 49:28.680
Michael,

49:29.680 --> 49:30.840
for the killings.

49:32.240 --> 49:34.280
Five for cutting and five for shooting.

49:34.360 --> 49:35.600
-No, Tommy.
-What?

49:36.040 --> 49:37.480
Tell me, eh?

49:38.080 --> 49:40.160
This is who I am!

49:41.280 --> 49:44.360
And this is all I can give you
for what you have given to me.

49:45.120 --> 49:47.960
For your hearts and your souls.

49:51.640 --> 49:54.840
Yesterday, I nearly lost my son.

49:57.040 --> 49:58.920
You should fucking understand that.

50:01.320 --> 50:03.560
For what, eh? For what?

50:03.640 --> 50:05.880
For this? For this?

50:08.400 --> 50:11.800
And I know that you all want
me to say that I will change,

50:11.880 --> 50:13.360
that this fucking business will change.

50:13.440 --> 50:16.000
But I've learnt something
these last few days.

50:16.080 --> 50:19.280
Those bastards. Those bastards

50:21.200 --> 50:22.600
are worse than us.

50:24.160 --> 50:27.800
Politicians, fucking judges,
lords and ladies.

50:27.880 --> 50:28.960
They are worse than us.

50:29.040 --> 50:32.240
And they will never admit us
to their palaces

50:32.800 --> 50:35.280
no matter how legitimate we become.

50:36.360 --> 50:37.760
Because of who we are,

50:38.360 --> 50:41.160
because of who we fucking are
because of where we are fucking from.

50:41.240 --> 50:42.320
Is that right, Ada?

50:43.400 --> 50:44.880
Our Ada knows.

50:46.040 --> 50:47.920
She got smart about revolution.

50:48.520 --> 50:52.280
And she knows you have to get
what you want your own way.

50:55.160 --> 50:58.320
Lizzie, I want it known, that money

50:59.440 --> 51:02.200
was for you
because some nights it was you

51:03.480 --> 51:06.320
who stopped my heart from breaking,
no-one else.

51:10.520 --> 51:12.480
And the rest of you,
you took the King's shilling.

51:16.320 --> 51:18.240
You took the King's fucking shilling.

51:19.720 --> 51:23.240
When you take the King's shilling,
the King expects you to kill.

51:26.000 --> 51:27.200
Right, Arthur?

51:28.240 --> 51:29.320
Yeah.

51:29.920 --> 51:31.840
That is how it works. Right, John?

51:38.800 --> 51:39.880
That's right.

51:41.440 --> 51:42.560
That's right, Pol.

51:44.560 --> 51:45.720
That is fucking right.

51:50.400 --> 51:51.480
Tommy...

51:53.560 --> 51:54.680
You've had a bad time.

51:56.000 --> 51:57.120
We understand.

52:00.080 --> 52:02.040
So at an alternative time,

52:05.880 --> 52:07.000
when we have all recovered...

52:09.040 --> 52:10.240
I would like

52:11.600 --> 52:12.920
to put before the family

52:13.960 --> 52:15.240
an alternative view

52:17.000 --> 52:20.160
of the future
of the Shelby Company Limited.

52:22.920 --> 52:24.880
A more hopeful view.

52:27.360 --> 52:28.600
(CHARLES CRYING)

52:30.080 --> 52:32.160
Which I, for one,
would quite like to hear.

52:33.120 --> 52:34.280
As would I.

52:35.120 --> 52:36.560
As would I.

52:43.560 --> 52:44.840
LINDA: Come on, Arthur.

52:45.440 --> 52:47.160
The train for the dock
leaves in one hour.

52:48.520 --> 52:50.400
Then we'll get the boat to New York,

52:51.560 --> 52:52.800
and it'll all be in the past.

53:28.480 --> 53:30.400
I will be off then, Tom.

53:31.800 --> 53:33.400
(ARTHUR SNIFFLES)

53:36.520 --> 53:37.800
I will see you, eh?

53:40.880 --> 53:42.960
I will see you, Brother.

53:52.560 --> 53:53.880
Bye, Curly.

53:55.920 --> 53:58.160
You can go,
but you won't get far, Arthur.

53:59.080 --> 54:01.480
Uh, all right, Tom.

54:01.560 --> 54:03.240
I spoke to Moss last night.

54:05.120 --> 54:07.280
He told me that the
Chief Constable of Birmingham

54:07.360 --> 54:10.720
has issued a warrant for your arrest.

54:11.200 --> 54:13.160
Murder, sedition,

54:13.800 --> 54:15.360
conspiracy to cause explosions.

54:16.960 --> 54:19.360
John, they're coming for you as well.

54:19.920 --> 54:23.080
Murder, conspiracy to cause explosions.

54:24.120 --> 54:25.200
Michael...

54:25.280 --> 54:27.360
ARTHUR: What the fuck?
TOMMY: ...for the murder of Hughes.

54:28.160 --> 54:29.240
Polly...

54:31.000 --> 54:33.040
ARTHUR: Wait a minute,
what the fuck are you...

54:33.120 --> 54:35.800
...the murder of
Chief Inspector Chester Campbell.

54:36.600 --> 54:38.120
JOHN: Why didn't you
fucking tell us, Tom?

54:38.200 --> 54:40.160
The people we betrayed last night,
they want to bring us down.

54:40.320 --> 54:43.880
They control the police,
they control the judges,

54:43.960 --> 54:46.680
the control the juries,
they control the jails.

54:46.760 --> 54:48.680
But they do not control...

54:48.840 --> 54:50.240
-JOHN: Look what they did to us.
-...the elected government.

54:50.320 --> 54:52.200
JOHN: Why didn't you tell us before?
ARTHUR: You are my brother.

54:52.280 --> 54:53.480
TOMMY: Listen to me.

54:53.640 --> 54:55.560
So I've made a deal.

54:55.640 --> 54:57.280
-They will hang us!
-In return

54:57.480 --> 54:59.280
for giving evidence against them.

54:59.480 --> 55:00.560
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
-ARTHUR: We will fucking hang.

55:00.640 --> 55:01.840
It is all taken care of.

55:01.920 --> 55:04.920
Lizzie, collect up the money
and bring it to the cellar.

55:05.520 --> 55:08.520
You will all get your money
in due course.

55:08.840 --> 55:10.760
When the police gets in, do not resist.

55:10.840 --> 55:14.000
You go with them,
and you do not say anything.

55:14.080 --> 55:15.280
Arthur,

55:15.440 --> 55:19.240
I have made a deal with people even
more powerful than our enemies.

55:19.360 --> 55:20.800
-LINDA: (SCREAMING) Arthur!
-Trust me, Brother, eh?

55:22.600 --> 55:23.920
Trust me.

55:24.040 --> 55:27.360
-ARTHUR: No, Linda...
-You did this deliberately!

55:27.440 --> 55:29.800
You made this happen to keep us!

55:29.920 --> 55:31.120
Come here. Come here.

55:31.880 --> 55:34.080
ARTHUR: Come on now, we
have to run. We have to run.

55:34.320 --> 55:35.920
(ALL CLAMOURING)

55:39.600 --> 55:40.880
ARTHUR: Fuck you!

55:41.880 --> 55:43.960
(CLAMOURING CONTINUES)

56:34.880 --> 56:35.880
(INAUDIBLE)

57:21.000 --> 57:23.960
(CLOCK TICKING)

57:35.280 --> 57:37.320
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

57:51.440 --> 57:55.920
<i># On a gathering storm
comes a tall handsome man</i>

57:56.000 --> 58:00.280
<i># In a dusty black coat
with a red right hand #</i>

58:00.304 --> 58:05.304
http://hiqve.com/
